 I thought it would not be very tasty since I put everything left in the freezer at random, but thanks to the frozen seafood, it was very tasty, so I replenished the supply of fish. I also found out that four pieces of dried hokke were only about 400 yen. I thought it was surprisingly cheap, so I bought some. I often make a one-pot dish with only vegetables and tofu because meat is too expensive and troublesome, but dried fish is not so troublesome, I thought.
 
