 *1236356005* shipping from amazon.co.uk
 I put this together in Japanese for Ichnozama's <a href='http://ikunozama.appspot.com/special/amazon.co.uk/kaimono/'>summary of how to shop at amazon.co.uk</a>.
 
 <hr>
 
 Shipping costs from amazon.co.uk to Japan are shown below.
 
 -1.49 pounds (approx. 210 yen) per CD/DVD
 -Books 2.99 pounds per book (about 420 yen)
 
 In addition to this, the entire packaging as a whole will cost the higher of the following: 293 yen if you buy only DVDs or CDs, or 698 yen if you also buy books.
 
 -CDs and DVDs 2.09 pounds (about 293 yen)
 -2.99 pounds (about 698 yen) per bottle
 
 So, if you buy 3 DVDs, you pay 210 * 3 + 293 = 923 yen; if you buy 1 DVD and 1 book, you pay 210 + 420 + 698 = 1328 yen.
 
 
 Shipping charges for used items on the Marketplace are separate from this and are as follows.
 
 -3.58 pounds (approx. 504 yen) per CD/DVD
 -Books 7.00 pounds per book (about 980 yen)
 
